Former Abia Governor Senator Uzor Kalu is expected to be in his hometown, Umuisi, Igbere in Bende Local Government Area of the state later today. The Nation can report it would be the first time Kalu would be home after he was jailed and released by Supreme Court in May. Kalu is slated to land at the Sam Mbadiwe Airport Imo, where he will take off to Umuahia, the state capital where he is expected to worship at the Mater Dei Catholic Cathedral Church, Azikiwe road in Umuahia North LGA. After the service, it was learnt he would head for his home town, where he will be received by his kinsmen and supporters. Details shortlyâ€¦